<section class="top">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3 title">
        <%= image_tag 'HeroTypeLP_1.svg' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="intro">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-2 phone">
        <%= image_tag 'phone.png' %>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-7 col-sm-offset-1 intro-container">
        <h1 class="heading">Local Knowledge. Authentic Adventures.</h1>

        <p class="body">
          Nile Travel makes planning incredible trips incredibly easy. Invite friends to collaborate in the trip
          planner, adding their own suggestions and comments, or choosing from a list of the best Local-Verified places
          and activities that best suit you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="river">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2 text">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-10 who">
            <h1>Who knows you better than your</h1>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6 friends">
            <h1>friends and family?</h1>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-3 col-sm-offset-3 no-one">
            <h1>No one.</h1>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="quip">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-8 text">
        <p class="body">
          Nile gathers travel suggestions in one place, taming the torrent of travel recommendations that comes with
          announcing your next trip on social media. By planning with friends who know you the best, and drawing on the
          insights of people who know the area the best, Nile travelers are confident that they’re making the very most
          of their trip.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-3 image">

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="team">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class=" col-xs-12 col-sm-4 col-sm-offset-4 who">
        <h1 class="heading">Who Is Nile?</h1>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2 images">
        <div class="row">
          <div class=" col-xs-6 col-sm-3 profile-image" data-name="scott">
            <div class="hexagon red">
              <div class="hexTop"></div>
              <div class="hexBottom"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-3 profile-image" data-name="derek">
            <div class="hexagon blue">
              <div class="hexTop"></div>
              <div class="hexBottom"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-3 profile-image" data-name="ian">
            <div class="hexagon brown">
              <div class="hexTop"></div>
              <div class="hexBottom"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-3 profile-image" data-name="tristram">
            <div class="hexagon red">
              <div class="hexTop"></div>
              <div class="hexBottom"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2 bios">
        <div class="bio" id="nile">
          <p class="col-xs-12 body">Nile, headquartered in the burgeoning tech market of Denver, Colorado, is the collaborative
            effort of
            Founders Derek Cann and Scott Brabson, UX/UI Designer Tristram Nelson, and Developer Ian Knox.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bio" id="scott">
          <h1 class="heading">Scott Brabson</h1>

          <h2>Founder & Head of Product</h2>

          <p class="col-xs-12 body">
            As Marketing Coordinator at Photobucket, Scott has been integral to successfully driving record revenue,
            growth and engagement across web and apps. A man of many hats, Scott also brings product expertise,
            constantly gathering and parsing user behavior and information, conducting A/B tests on top of A/B tests,
            launching the Photobucket App’s first onboarding campaign, and doing so in tandem with product teams. A
            startup man at heart (and an after hours renaissance man), Scott has dipped his toes into small business
            with the successful launch of Forest & Filament, a handmade furniture company that continues to be
            profitable, and brings his passion for small business and product that just makes sense to Nile Travel.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bio" id="derek">
          <h1 class="heading">Derek Cann</h1>

          <h2>Founder & President</h2>

          <p class="col-xs-12 body">
            Derek brings over ten years of organizational, people and product management experience to the Nile
            management team. As the Marketing Manager at Photobucket, Derek led a team which brought three mobile apps
            and two website products to market posting record growth and revenue figures. Derek previously founded Beat
            of Travel (.com), a travel and lifestyle website which partnered with travel industry leaders including
            Virgin Vacations and Key West Express. An alumni of the University of Colorado Denver School of Business,
            Derek earned a Masters of Marketing with specializations in Internet Marketing and Brand Management in
            Spring of 2014.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bio" id="ian">
          <h1 class="heading">Ian Knox</h1>

          <h2>Director of Engineering</h2>

          <p class="col-xs-12 body">
            Ian brings a diverse skill set to Nile, his fields of study include History, Computer Science, Applied
            Mathematics, and Civil Engineering. A graduate of Galvanize's gSchool in Denver, Ian is a technical polyglot
            and developer generalist. Integrating useful and relevant technologies across both web a
            nd mobile platforms are his meat and potatoes.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bio" id="tristram">
          <h1 class="heading">Tristram Nelson</h1>

          <h2> Director of User Experience/Design</h2>

          <p class="col-xs-12 body">
            As a Senior UX/UI designer at Photobucket, Tristram led the design of the new Photobucket Print Shop product
            which exceeded print revenue goals (+30K) first month after launch. A content consultant for over five years
            for Intrepid Travel, he created advertising and promotions for global distribution, and created UX and UI
            design for both TravelStore and Southwind Travels. Tristram is an Alumni of RMCAD with a Bachelors of Fine
            Arts in Communications Design.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2 vision">
        <%= image_tag 'NileLogoBlueRedLP_1.svg' %>
        <h1 class="heading">Our Vision</h1>

        <p class="body">Nile is a public benefit corporation. We want you to have amazing travels without the hassle of
          having to
          weed through deceptive reviews or a mess of suggestions. We don't believe in selling user data. We do believe
          we should be low impace campers leaving the world (and web) a better place than we found
          it. <%= link_to 'Read our manifesto>>', '#' %></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
